metadata.name: Bloc.Plan #46
metadata.description:
Working as an architect and interior designer daily, I always find that creating space is something interesting. Especially a block plan. As an architectural drawing, it serves to inform the viewer of the presence or absence of a space by composing positive and negative spaces on the site. Through this, I found out that block plan can be a captivating visual art as well.

Press [s] to save captured image

created using p5.js
dirbots - Aug22

metadata.name: Updraft #241
metadata.description:
UPDRAFT seeks to reproduce the beauty of tornadoes and other vortices in a minimalist style and simple shapes, thus highlighting the purity of the lines of these fascinating objects.

If the tornado of life scares you, remember that while you will probably be a little shaken and confused on your journey, you will end up at the top of it. That's the beauty of the updraft.

[S] or [Double-Tap] when viewing in full screen to save a 4000x4000 PNG image

Artist: Estienne
August 2022
Made with p5.js
Best viewed on Chrome or Chromium-based browsers

metadata.name: Path #31
metadata.description:
A degen has no goal, only path. But how will he go this path? 
Through the forest, by train or walking in the desert?

metadata.name: Divide by Circle #236
metadata.description:
An experiment with subdivision, cubes, and a circle.
There are many parameters and special features.
Click to randomize divisions with the same settings.
Unminted editions over 100 will be burnt after 24 hours.

By Frank Force @KilledByAPixel
Made with JavaScript and Three.js

Live Mode Controls
1 - Save 2048x2048 png with SSAA
2 - Toggle noise
3 - Toggle animation
4 - Randomize every 10 seconds
